Bafana Bafana moved one step closer to 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification after thrashing Congo Brazzaville 5-0 at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium
Pre-Game Insights: Bafana Bafana midfielder Themba Zwane will achieve a milestone should he play against Congo Brazzaville in a crunch 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifier at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium in Gqeberha tonight
Captain and goalkeeper Ronwen Williams returned between the sticks after he missed last month’s 2-2 home draw against Uganda and 3-2 win away against South Sudan due to injury
Bafana Bafana coach Hugo Broos has reiterated that they cannot afford to underestimate Congo-Brazzaville based on the challenges they have been going through back home

This was Teboho Mokoena’s party. As such, he was duly the Man of the Match and given a standing ovation when he was withdrawn.

In the News Today: South Africa’s national soccer team, Bafana Bafana, is all set to take on Congo Brazzaville in a highly anticipated 2025 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) qualifier. The match will be held at Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium in Gqeberha on Friday, 11 October 2024, at 7 PM.
Others: In the News Today: Teboho Mokoena was the star of the show on Friday evening as the South African anchor scored a brace to contribute to a clinical 5-0 win over Congo at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium in Gqeberha (Port Elizabeth).
In the News Today: Goals were the order of the day in Friday’s set of 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers as the likes of South Africa, Senegal, Cameroon and Ivory Coast won big on matchday three.
In the News Today: Bafana Bafana ended their latest AFCON qualifier gameweek in 2nd position in Group K following a 5-0 win against Congo at the Nelson Mandela Bay Stadium on Friday night.
